<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 31 at 2:33PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Periods of light snow to continue this afternoon across North
Central Montana...
At 220 pm, the cold front has moved south out of North Central
Montana, as temperatures in the 20s fall into the teens this
afternoon.
Periods of light to moderate snow will continue through the
afternoon, with additional accumulations remaining less than one
inch.
Northerly winds continue to gust into the 30 to 40 mph range, with
a few gusts possibly reaching 50 mph.
Blowing snow may still reduce visibility to less than one mile at
times, and many roads are now icy. Be prepared for changing
visibility and road conditions.</description>
